    "Previously, the most popular approach for visualizing RNA velocity has been the projection of the high-dimensional vector field onto a low-dimensional latent space representation 7.",
    "With CellRank 2, we generalize this concept to any kernel based on a k-nearest-neighbor graph, that is, the PseudotimeKernel, CytoTRACEKernel and Veloci-tyKernel.",
    "The projection for a given cell is calculated as follows: Consider a transition matrix T, cell j with neighborhood N(j) and k j neighbors and latent representation z j.",
